I have removed the main new part to another PR (#17522). The present PR consists of basic useful lemmas.
I don't understand what the `large-import` tag means, because it doesn't seem I have modified `import`s.

> I don't understand what the `large-import` tag means, because it doesn't seem I have modified `import`s.

[This comment](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/17046#issuecomment-2367787247) by the bot (which gets updated on each commit) tells you precisely which imports changed (and indeed you add an import in GroupTheory.Perm.Support). Please revert spurious changes in other files
I don't understand *why*. The new code has 3 other approaches, one works, the two other don't.

The problem is the coercion from `MulEquiv` to normal functions does not go through `Equiv` (at least not synctactically), so `rw` sees no `Equiv` in the goal. It works if you do `  rw [â EquivLike.coe_coe, Set.preimage_equiv_eq_image_symm]`.

There seems to be some API lacking around cardinal of preimages. In the meantime, I think the following defeq-abuse is the nicest proof we can do:
```suggestion
  rw [Subgroup.centralizer_eq_comap_stabilizer]
  rfl
```
Can these not go earlier? Actually, same question about much more of this file

I dispatched these lemmas in Data/Set/Basic and Data/Finset/Basic and Order/Disjoint.
For the rest, I'll have a look at what can be done.
@Ruben-VandeVelde : unfortunately, adding 4 more lines to Data/Finset/Basic made it be larger than the 3100-line limit.
